"{\"uid\": \"news-herald.com-2024-06-21-lake-catholic-alum-matt-ludwig-advances-to-the-finals-of-the-olympic-trials-pole-vault\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"e-Edition  Sign up for email newsletters    Sign up for email newsletters  e-Edition  TRENDING:  Matt Ludwig is one good day away from advancing to the 2024 Summer Olympics in France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 183, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A graduate of Lake Catholic, Ludwig was one of 12 pole vaulters who advanced in the preliminary round of competition on June 21 at the Olympic Trials in Eugene, Ore.\", \"from\": 185, \"to\": 350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 199, \"end\": 212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Catholic_High_School\", \"score\": 0.9999999913752617, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lake Catholic\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3914\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Catholic_High_School\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lake_Catholic_High_School\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The competition resumes on Sunday, June 23, with the top three finishers advancing to the Olympics representing the United States starting July 26.\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 467, \"end\": 480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9856353485477322, \"rank\": 0.010622556418010055, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ludwig, 27, cleared all four of his heights on the first try on Jun 21, clearing 17-8 1/2, 18-0 1/2, 18-4 1/2 and 18-6 1/2.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He, along with Sam Kendricks, passed at the 18-8 1/4 height as others in the competition struggled and most of them were eliminated at that height.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 771, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 639, \"end\": 652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kendricks\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sam Kendricks\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kendricks\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sam_Kendricks\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Heading into the finals on June 23, Kendricks and Ludwig are tied for sixth.\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's because five other vaulters who did not pass at the 18-8 1/4 height cleared the mark, Austin Miller on his first try and the group of Chris Nilson, Keaton Daniel, Jacob Wooten and Zachery Bradford all clearing it after a miss.\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 1083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austin_S._Miller\", \"score\": 0.9999999982903773, \"rank\": 1.7096279541504999e-09, \"text\": \"Austin Miller\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austin_S._Miller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Austin_S._Miller\"}, {\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nilson_Antonio\", \"score\": 0.9999810768880355, \"rank\": 1.5252033351652493e-05, \"text\": \"Nilson\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nilson_Antonio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nilson_Antonio\"}, {\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradford_City_A.F.C.\", \"score\": 0.5764913179106557, \"rank\": 0.7023364730426706, \"text\": \"Bradford\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradford_City_A.F.C.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bradford_City_A.F.C.\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ludwig is aiming for a return trip the the Olympics after participating in the 2020 games in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1085, \"to\": 1184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1178, \"end\": 1183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8363700505246733, \"rank\": 0.19535498516119054, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ironically, the man Ludwig is tied with - Kendricks - is partly responsible for the berth in Tokyo, as Kendricks tested positive for COVID-19, which allowed Ludwig to move up from his alternate role to the Olympic roster.\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8363700505246733, \"rank\": 0.19535498516119054, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1318, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.980479968638865, \"rank\": 0.011962316264577678, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copyright \\u00a9 2025 MediaNews Group\", \"from\": 1408, \"to\": 1440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1425, \"end\": 1440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"MediaNews Group\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Digital_First_Media\"}]}]}"